cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the development and evaluation of diagnosis models for patient-facing online symptom checkers. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Electronic Health Record (EHR) data, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
